v1.2  (Feb 2011)\
- Split Editing\
Individual splits are now fully editable, including add, change and delete.  Also, you can now change the base units and split modes for any event in your database.  It is now easy to fix timing glitches.\
\
- Lap Mode\
This new mode allows you to record events where the intervals are not tied to a specific distance.\
\
- Furlong Mode\
Furlong mode is for horse racing.  Distances are displayed in fractions of a mile instead of yards.\
\
- Running Time/Lap Time Swap\
Tap the Splitwatch main time display to swap the running time with the lap time.\
\
- More Event Summary Info\
In addition to closing splits, Splitwatch now provides split summary info with Min, Max, and Avg lap times.\
\
- Distance Labels\
Distance labels for events where the lap interval is 25y or 50y is now cleaner (no mile breakdown)\
